Unemployment in the EuropeanCommunity fell in March to 16.8 mln from 17 mln in Februarythanks to an improvement in the weather, the EC's statisticsagency Eurostat said.    It said the number of jobless fell in all 12 Communitymember states as weather conditions improved, though France,Italy and Spain saw declines of less than one pct.    There was also a particularly large drop in the number ofjobless under-25s in all states except Italy, where 19,300 moreyoung people were unemployed in March than in the month before. REUTER&#3;